Runes
A Necromancer's amulet has two runes carved into it. These runes are the
rune of death, and the rune of blight. These runes contain the same
ancient magic ~>Alarian<~ used a millenium ago. Some Necromantic spells
dervive their power from death or blight. These spells (indicated by a 
'D' or 'B', respectively, in ~>necspells<~) can drain a rune of its power
momentarily, adding an extra effect to the spell. Over time, these runes
will recharge.
